    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.73-74_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">73</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">O R P H E U S   R E C O R D S 
                        <lb/>
                    POST OFFICE BOX 24236           LOS ANGELES 24, CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener> 
                <p>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt, noted author of <hi rend="caps">A CYCLE OF THE WEST</hi>, has recently been recorded reading excerpts from "The Song of Three Friends." This recording on a 12 inch vinylite <hi rend="caps">LP</hi> of the author reading his own work is now available to faculty members, libraries and former students of Mr. Neihardt at a 10% discount. The regular price of this record is $3.98. You may now order it for only $3.58 postpaid.</p>
                
                <p>Mr. Neihardt has received far too many prizes and honors for his poetry, scholarship, teaching and criticism to list here. The Christian Science Monitor said of "The Song of Three Friends:"
                    <lb/>
                    For this high endeavor to reveal in epic strain the heroic qualities of courage and devotion in the American pioneer we must pay our homage to John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt.</p>
                
                <p>Of his reading, the National Council of Teachers of English (St. Louis Convention) said:
                    <lb/>
                    It was an unforgettable experience to hear Mr. Neihardt interpret his vigorous poetry of the West. He charmed his audience, and he made every person in the large, crowded auditorium his audience, for his voice carried without effort. He should read much to students of literature in order that they may learn that poetry is alive and compelling.</p>
                
                <p>Those who know Mr. Neihardt or have heard him read will not want to miss this opportunity to have a record of him reading excerpts from "The Song of Three Friends." Mail the enclosed post card now and receive your copy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Sanford D. Gray</signed>
                
                    <signed>Sanford D. Gray
                    ORPHEUS RECORDS</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
